Review saved. Here's the summary:

**4 findings across the nsqlookupd files:**

| # | Type | File | Line | Severity | Description |
|---|------|------|------|----------|-------------|
| 1 | BUG | `apps/nsqlookupd/main.go` | 84 | Medium | Missing format verb in `logFatal` — `err` is never printed to the operator |
| 2 | BUG | `nsqlookupd/nsqlookupd.go` | 44-46 | Low | TCP listener leaked if HTTP listener fails in `New()` |
| 3 | BUG | `nsqlookupd/registration_db.go` | 48-55 | Medium | Data race on `Producer.tombstoned`/`tombstonedAt` — written by HTTP tombstone handler, read by `FilterByActive`, both after DB lock is released |
| 4 | QUESTION | `nsqlookupd/lookup_protocol_v1.go` | 250 | Medium | `log.Fatalf` in `IDENTIFY()` request handler crashes entire process, bypassing cleanup |

**Overall: NEEDS DISCUSSION** — the tombstone data race is the most significant finding.
